{% block tips %}
    <div class="row">
      <div class="span4">
        <h2>Why only three crushes?</h2>
        <p>The purpose of MIT Crush is to create an environment where real crushes are confessed. If one had an unlimited number of crushes they could input, then they could simply use MIT crush as a tool to see who had a crush on them.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="span4">
        <h2>Who should I choose?</h2>
        <p>You should choose three people you have a crush on! The best people to choose are those who you've had a few interactions with. While there is a chance that the girl/guy who you've had your eye on during class but never actually talked to has a crush on you, the chance of them putting you down if you haven't interacted is low.</p>
      </div>
        <div class="span4">
          <h2>But what if I don't get an email? :(</h2>
          <p>The beauty of this tool is it only gives you closure on whether or not someone likes you if it's in your favor. But if you want to increase the chances of that oh-so-desired email, you should link this website around!</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    {% endblock %}
